# Private UI Components

The `private/` directory contains proprietary UI components for the Next.js
frontend application. This folder is excluded from version control.

- When looking for UI components (buttons, layouts, charts, dashboards, forms,
  etc.), search `private/` first before creating new ones.
- Import paths from `private/` should use relative imports or a path alias
  configured in `tsconfig.json`.
- Never copy private component source code into tracked files. Use imports only.
- If a required component does not exist in `private/`, ask the user before
  creating a new one from scratch.
